{"timestamp": "2026-05-27 18:00:25,372", "level": "INFO", "logger": "flow.execution", "module": "flow", "function": "run_async", "line": 205, "message": " - task0: ```text\n1. Job Title:\n   - Standardized Title: Workflow Planning Agent\n\n2. Required Skills:\n   a. Technical Skills:\n      - Natural Language Processing (NLP)\n      - Text Analysis\n      - Data Extraction\n   b. Soft Skills:\n      - Analytical Skills\n      - Communication Skills\n      - Workflow Management\n\n3. Preferred Skills:\n   a. Technical Skills:\n      - Machine Learning (ML)\n      - Email Automation\n   b. Soft Skills:\n      - Prioritization\n      - Adaptability\n\n4. Years of Experience:\n   - Minimum: 0 years\n   - Preferred: 1+ years\n\n5. Educational Requirements:\n   - Required: None specified\n   - Preferred: Bachelor's degree in Computer Science or related field\n\n6. Key Responsibilities:\n   - Responsibility 1: Analyze job descriptions and candidate resumes.\n   - Responsibility 2: Plan and manage the workflow for candidate evaluation.\n   - Responsibility 3: Extract key information for each task.\n   - Responsibility 4: Send emails as needed.\n   - Responsibility 5: Score candidate responses and generate final evaluation report.\n\n7. Department and Seniority:\n   - Department: N/A\n   - Seniority Level: N/A\n\n8. Location & Remote Policy:\n   - Location: N/A\n   - Remote: N/A\n\n9. Compensation Range:\n   - Salary: N/A\n   - Bonus/Equity: N/A\n\n10. Language Inclusivity Flags:\n    - Vague Terms: None identified.\n    - Potential Bias: None identified.\n\n11. Evaluation Criteria:\n    a. Technical Assessments:\n       - Accuracy of job description and resume analysis.\n       - Efficiency of workflow planning.\n    b. Behavioral / Soft-Skills:\n       - Clarity and effectiveness of communication.\n       - Ability to prioritize tasks.\n    c. Cultural Fit:\n       - Alignment with task objectives and downstream goals.\n```\n"}
{"timestamp": "2026-05-27 18:00:25,373", "level": "INFO", "logger": "flow.execution", "module": "flow", "function": "run_async", "line": 205, "message": " - task1: Candidate Resume Analysis Report\n\n----------------------------------------\nCandidate Resume Analysis Report\nCandidate Name: John Doe\n----------------------------------------\n\nStep 1: Resume Parsing\n- Sections parsed:\n  • Professional Summary\n  • Technical Skills\n  • Professional Experience\n  • Education\n  • Certifications\n\nStep 2: Skills Extraction\n- Programming Languages:\n  • Python\n  • JavaScript (ES6+)\n  • Java\n- Frameworks & Libraries:\n  • Django\n  • Flask\n  • React\n  • Node.js\n- Databases:\n  • PostgreSQL\n  • MongoDB\n- DevOps & Cloud:\n  • AWS (EC2, S3, Lambda)\n  • Docker\n  • Kubernetes\n- Tools & Methodologies:\n  • Git\n  • Jenkins\n  • RESTful APIs\n  • GraphQL\n  • Agile/Scrum\n\nStep 3: Experience Extraction\n- Software Engineer, Acme Corp (2019–Present)\n  • Designed and implemented RESTful services in Django for a high-traffic e-commerce platform.\n  • Developed React components, improving UI load speed by 30%.\n  • Automated CI/CD pipelines with Jenkins and Docker, reducing deployment errors by 40%.\n- Web Developer, Beta Solutions (2016–2019)\n  • Built Node.js microservices for real-time data processing integrated with MongoDB.\n  • Migrated legacy systems to AWS Lambda, cutting operational costs by 25%.\n  • Collaborated in Agile sprints to deliver features bi-weekly.\n\nStep 4: Requirement Matching\n- Job requires: Full-stack web dev, cloud deployment, CI/CD, Agile process.\n- Direct matches:\n  • Backend: Python/Django experience.\n  • Frontend: React/Node.js expertise.\n  • Cloud: Hands-on AWS (EC2, S3, Lambda).\n  • DevOps: Docker, Kubernetes, Jenkins.\n  • Methodology: Agile/Scrum collaboration.\n\nStep 5: Strong Alignments\n- Python & Django: 4+ years building backend services.\n- React & Node.js: 5 years of full-stack projects.\n- AWS Cloud: Deployed services on EC2 and Lambda in production.\n- CI/CD: Automated pipelines with Jenkins and Docker.\n- Agile/Scrum: Active participant in cross-functional sprints.\n\nStep 6: Gaps & Missing Requirements\n- TypeScript: No experience recorded. (Minor)\n- GraphQL: Mentioned but no project details. (Minor)\n- Mobile App Development: Not present. (Minor)\n\nStep 7: Transferable Skills\n- Docker & Kubernetes: Container orchestration transferable to any microservice architecture.\n- Data analysis basics: Ability to leverage data for feature optimization.\n\nStep 8: Scoring\n- Skills Alignment Score: 90/100\n- Experience Relevance Score: 85/100\n- Overall Match Score: 88/100\n\nStep 9: Overall Fit Determination\n- Categorized as: Strong Fit\n- Rationale: High alignment in core full-stack and cloud skills; minor gaps are non-critical.\n\nStep 10: Recruiter Notes\nJohn brings a robust full-stack background with proven cloud deployments and CI/CD automation. His hands-on AWS and DevOps expertise will accelerate our infrastructure goals. Minor gaps in TypeScript and mobile can be addressed through targeted training. Recommend moving forward to technical interview.\n\n----------------------------------------\nEnd of Report\n----------------------------------------\n"}
{"timestamp": "2026-05-27 18:00:25,373", "level": "INFO", "logger": "flow.execution", "module": "flow", "function": "run_async", "line": 205, "message": " - task2: ```text\n1. Analyze Job Description:\n   - Parse job description to identify required skills, responsibilities, and evaluation criteria.\n   - Output: Extracted job requirements (skills, experience, education, responsibilities).\n\n2. Analyze Candidate Resume:\n   - Parse candidate resume to identify skills, experience, and qualifications.\n   - Output: Resume analysis report including skills, experience, and a fit score.\n\n3. Initial Candidate Screening:\n   - Compare candidate skills and experience against job requirements.\n   - Determine initial candidate fit based on skills alignment score.\n\n4. Send Interview Invitation Email:\n   - Draft and send an interview invitation email to the candidate.\n   - Include details about the interview time, format, and topics to be covered.\n   - Subject Line: Interview Invitation - Workflow Planning Agent\n   - Email Body:\n     - Greeting: Dear John Doe,\n     - Body: We are pleased to invite you to an interview for the Workflow Planning Agent position at our company. Your skills and experience align well with the requirements of the role. The interview is scheduled for [Date] at [Time] via [Platform]. During the interview, we will discuss your experience with NLP, text analysis, data extraction, and your approach to workflow management.\n     - Call-to-action: Please confirm your availability at your earliest convenience.\n     - Closing: Best regards, [Your Name/Company Name]\n   - Tone Tag: Semi-Formal\n   - Personalization Tokens Used: Candidate Name, Date, Time, Platform, Your Name/Company Name\n\n5. Conduct Technical Interview:\n   - Conduct the technical interview, focusing on key skills and experience.\n   - Assess candidate's practical knowledge and problem-solving abilities.\n   - Record candidate responses and observations.\n\n6. Score Candidate Responses:\n   - Evaluate candidate responses based on predefined scoring criteria.\n   - Assign scores for technical skills, soft skills, and overall performance.\n\n7. Generate Final Evaluation Report:\n   - Compile all data, including resume analysis, interview feedback, and scoring.\n   - Generate a final evaluation report summarizing the candidate's strengths and weaknesses.\n   - Include an overall recommendation (hire, no hire, further evaluation).\n```"}
{"timestamp": "2026-05-27 18:00:25,373", "level": "INFO", "logger": "flow.execution", "module": "flow", "function": "run_async", "line": 205, "message": " - task3: ```text\n1. Analyze Job Description:\n   - Parse job description to identify required skills, responsibilities, and evaluation criteria.\n   - Output: Extracted job requirements (skills, experience, education, responsibilities).\n\n2. Analyze Candidate Resume:\n   - Parse candidate resume to identify skills, experience, and qualifications.\n   - Output: Resume analysis report including skills, experience, and a fit score.\n\n3. Initial Candidate Screening:\n   - Compare candidate skills and experience against job requirements.\n   - Determine initial candidate fit based on skills alignment score.\n\n4. Send Interview Invitation Email:\n   - Draft and send an interview invitation email to the candidate.\n   - Include details about the interview time, format, and topics to be covered.\n   - Subject Line: Interview Invitation - Workflow Planning Agent\n   - Email Body:\n     - Greeting: Dear John Doe,\n     - Body: We are pleased to invite you to an interview for the Workflow Planning Agent position at our company. Your skills and experience align well with the requirements of the role. The interview is scheduled for [Date] at [Time] via [Platform]. During the interview, we will discuss your experience with NLP, text analysis, data extraction, and your approach to workflow management.\n     - Call-to-action: Please confirm your availability at your earliest convenience.\n     - Closing: Best regards, [Your Name/Company Name]\n   - Tone Tag: Semi-Formal\n   - Personalization Tokens Used: Candidate Name, Date, Time, Platform, Your Name/Company Name\n\n5. Conduct Technical Interview:\n   - Round: Technical\n   - Question: \"Describe your experience with Natural Language Processing (NLP). What NLP techniques have you used, and for what purposes?\"\n   - Competency Tested: NLP, Technical Skills\n   - Ideal Answer Indicators: Mention of specific NLP techniques (e.g., sentiment analysis, topic modeling, named entity recognition), tools/libraries used (e.g., NLTK, spaCy, transformers), and specific projects where NLP was applied.\n   - Follow-up Probes: \"Can you provide an example of a challenging NLP problem you solved?\", \"How do you evaluate the performance of your NLP models?\"\n\n   - Round: Technical\n   - Question: \"Explain your approach to text analysis. How do you handle unstructured text data, and what methods do you use to extract meaningful information?\"\n   - Competency Tested: Text Analysis, Data Extraction\n   - Ideal Answer Indicators: Discussion of preprocessing steps (e.g., cleaning, tokenization, stemming), feature extraction techniques (e.g., TF-IDF, word embeddings), and methods for identifying patterns or insights in text data.\n   - Follow-up Probes: \"What are some common challenges you face when working with unstructured text?\", \"How do you ensure the accuracy and reliability of your text analysis results?\"\n\n   - Round: Technical\n   - Question: \"Describe a project where you automated data extraction from documents or web pages. What tools and techniques did you use?\"\n   - Competency Tested: Data Extraction, Automation\n   - Ideal Answer Indicators: Explanation of tools like Beautiful Soup, Scrapy, or regular expressions, as well as strategies for handling different data formats and website structures.\n   - Follow-up Probes: \"How did you handle errors or changes in the data source?\", \"What steps did you take to ensure the extracted data was accurate and complete?\"\n\n   - Round: Technical\n   - Question: \"How would you design a workflow to analyze customer reviews and identify key areas for product improvement?\"\n   - Competency Tested: Workflow Management, Analytical Skills\n   - Ideal Answer Indicators: A structured approach including data collection, preprocessing, NLP techniques (e.g., sentiment analysis, topic modeling), analysis of results, and actionable recommendations.\n   - Follow-up Probes: \"How would you prioritize different areas for improvement?\", \"How would you measure the impact of your recommendations?\"\n\n   - Round: Technical\n   - Question: \"How familiar are you with email automation? Describe any experience you have in automating email sending or processing.\"\n   - Competency Tested: Email Automation\n   - Ideal Answer Indicators: Mention of experience with tools like SendGrid, Mailgun, or AWS SES, as well as knowledge of email protocols (SMTP, IMAP) and techniques for handling bounces or unsubscribes.\n   - Follow-up Probes: \"How do you ensure that automated emails are compliant with regulations like GDPR?\", \"How do you track the performance of your email campaigns?\"\n\n6. Score Candidate Responses:\n   - Evaluate candidate responses based on predefined scoring criteria.\n   - Assign scores for technical skills, soft skills, and overall performance.\n\n7. Generate Final Evaluation Report:\n   - Compile all data, including resume analysis, interview feedback, and scoring.\n   - Generate a final evaluation report summarizing the candidate's strengths and weaknesses.\n   - Include an overall recommendation (hire, no hire, further evaluation).\n```"}
